Projects Worked : 

Project 1 : Catering Services : This project is about calculating the loss the airline incur during on-board Catering Services and help them uplift the correct number of perishable items on board to cut down on their costs. The data showed that they were incurring huge loss per person on board by not predicting correctly the demand of the items. We calculated the actual loss per customer using Linear Regression and using the mean and standard deviation we calculated the predicted number of quantities of each perishable item that needs to uplift on the flight. 

Project 2 : Anomaly Detection : This project is about finding anomaly in the CPU usage in the VM. The parameters were CPU Usage, Memory, Net Bytes and Number of Users. I used the Multi Variate Gaussian Distribution to find the probability of all the associated variables and then multiply these probability at each data point and then using a small value epsilon for the probability, we decide if a particular data point is an anomaly in the dataset.

Project 3 : Topic Modelling : This project is help the HR find the best possible resume for the given Job Description (JD) . HRs generally receive lots of resume for a particular JD, we helped them to rank the resume using Topic Modelling. Each resume is considered as a document and we looked at the skills and role and responsibilities section of the resume and group all the resume into different topics using LDA. Next we used Nearest Neighbor Algorithm to find the rank the grouped resume for a particular JD.

Project 4 : Risk Sensing : This project is about calculating the risk score for doing a business in a particular company. The raw score of various risk factors for a particular country is converted into single risk score value of doing business with that country. Logistic Regression is used to convert the various risk score between 0 and 1 and then using Leontief model to calculate the risk score when a risk is triggered. 
		
Project 5 : Twitter Data Analysis : This project is about analysis of tweets after downloading the tweets based on the taxonomy of Country and Risk Factors. Tweets are then cleaned and clusters are created after removing the stop words. These clusters are then used as Decision making Heuristics which will calculate if the risk has got triggered or not. Combination of TFIDF and LDA is used.

Project 6 : Classification of Legal Documents : In this project the entire Legal document is classified into SLA and Non-SLA statements using algorithms such as LinearSVC, Random Forest, GBM, Adaboost, Decision Tree, Naive Bayes etc. and then performance parameters like Sensitivity, Specificity, Kappa, ROC, Confusion Matrix and Accuracy are calculated to find which algorithm is working best. Combination of TFIDF and Word2Vec is also used.

Project 7 : KREG Project : In this project several sections of the documents were classified into 7 different category, such that all the records belong to one or multiple classes among the 7 category. The task is to predict the probability for all records belonging to all the 7 class and then take the top 3 probability to classify the record to a specific class. We mark prediction as success if the any of the Top 3 class the model predicts is same as the actual class of the record.

Project 8 : Mede Analytics Project : In this project each sentence of a legal document was classified to section to which it belongs. By doing that we had 15 category and the task is to predict the class of the section to which the sentence belongs. This is resolved by calculating probability of each record using Logistic regression for each class and then using the features as probability of prior, current and next record to predict the class to which the statement belongs.

Project 9 : STAR : In this project team provided support to SGTS user which offers financial services to the SONY sister companies. The client used to provide us financial data such as Foreign Exchange deals, Currency Option Deals, Money Market deals and the team used to calculate the risk of each deal based on the future currency rates using moving average method and report back to the client. 

Various other projects worked on Mainframe are : 

Crew Management and Timekeeping Solution for client Union Pacific Rail Road.
Credit Risk Management for client Lloyds Banking Group.
Data Conversion and Migration Project for client Universal American Financial Corporation.
Supply Chain Services for client Gexpro.
